range purpose is to collect comparabale information on as many polities as possible in order to facilitate the development of a richer theory to guide language policy and planning in other polities that undertake the development of a national policy on languages. This volumes is part of an areal series which is committed to providing descriptions of language planning and policy in countries around the world.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Apr 2022) 0aLanguage planningzEurope. 0aLanguage policyzEurope. 7aLANGUAGE ARTS & DISCIPLINES / Linguistics / Sociolinguistics.2bisacsh  aCzech Republic.  aEuropean Union.  aNorthern Ireland.  alanguage planning.  alanguage policy.  alinguistic diversity.  anon-indigenous languages.1 aBaldauf Jr, Richard B, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aBaldauf, Richard B., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aChríost, Diarmait Mac Giolla, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aEls, T.J.M. van, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKaplan, Robert B, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aKaplan, Robert B., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aNekvapil, Jirí, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aNeustupný, J.V., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertMultiLingual Matters Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2015z978311066313608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertMultiLingual Matters eBook Package Backlist 2000-2014z978311060671340uhttps://doi.org/10.21832/978185359814240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781853598142423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781853598142/original  a978-3-11-